# Flutter Login App — Cursor Rules

## Project
- Flutter 3.29.x / Dart 3.x mobile app
- Professional login UI with blue/cyan gradient wave design
- Repo: https://github.com/Prakhar2025/flutter-app

## Design Rules (DO NOT BREAK)
- Primary gradient: #005BEA → #00C6FB
- Font: ALWAYS use GoogleFonts.poppins() — never plain TextStyle()
- Card: borderRadius 28, white background, soft blue shadow
- Input fields: borderRadius 14, grey fill (#F9F9F9), cyan focus border
- Buttons: full-width, gradient, borderRadius 14, cyan glow shadow
- Wave header: CustomClipper<Path> (_WaveClipper) — keep as is

## Code Conventions
- All screens: StatefulWidget
- Navigation: PageRouteBuilder + SlideTransition ONLY (no MaterialPageRoute)
- Animations: FadeInDown for header text, FadeInUp for form card
- All form fields must have validator: functions
- Colors: Use hex Color(0xFF...) — never Colors.blue/red/green generic names

## File Structure
- lib/main.dart — entry point
- lib/screens/login_screen.dart — Login UI (source of truth for design)
- lib/screens/signup_screen.dart — Sign Up UI
- New screens: copy wave header + card pattern from login_screen.dart

## What's Done
- Login + Sign Up screens with full validation
- Smooth animations and page transitions
- Google Fonts (Poppins)

## Next Steps
- Firebase Authentication
- Home screen post-login
- Dark mode
- Splash screen
